      "how_far": "Clears the game (\u901a\u5173) \u2014 defeats the full sequence of ~19.5M-HP, 5-layer bosses. On large fresh-seed benchmarks it wins ~61-65% (mean eval ~1.14, avg win around step ~56k of 90k); most non-wins reach 75-95% progress (an 'almost win' on a late boss).",
      "failure_modes": [
        "Late-boss death (biggest category, ~23%): survive several bosses then get caught by a very dense late-boss bullet pattern at high progress",
        "Early-boss death (~12%): reach the first boss underleveled/low-eHP and die in its opening barrage",
        "Rare timeout (~4%) when DPS ramps too slowly to finish every boss within 90k steps",
        "Boss body contact does ~2700 dmg (near-lethal) and bosses roam/dive"
      ],
      "lessons": [
        "The game is a sequence of multi-layer bosses; auto-fire is straight-up only, so x-alignment with the boss is mandatory to deal damage (the boss is 120px wide, so a ~56px free-dodge band still connects)",
        "Boss layers fall faster as you level (DPS compounds), so the whole game is gated on survival",
        "A multi-tick trajectory ROLLOUT (does committing to this heading get me trapped/cornered?) dodges far better than a 1-tick 'hold position' danger model \u2014 it roughly doubled the win rate",
        "Movement momentum (favor continuing your heading) cut jitter and added ~15% win rate",
        "When surrounded, seek the FIELD CENTER (max escape room) instead of staying glued to the boss column \u2014 stops the boss from herding you into a wall",
        "Effective HP (recharging shield + heal-overflow->max-HP snowball) lets you survive long enough to win; over-prioritizing survival, though, just causes timeouts",
        "The boss variant depends on the action sequence (RNG), so robustness to all patterns matters more than fitting one seed; per-seed variance is huge, so evaluate changes via A/B on 120+ identical seeds"
      ],
      "attempts_used": 55
    },
